79b9fd77-bdb7-4c47-b4aa-7af09961cfde.1452542e-8965-403b-85fd-1dfaacfaae93.prompt=Notification option\: 79b9fd77-bdb7-4c47-b4aa-7af09961cfde.37399e4b-d5ab-4db9-80cb-da7948c9dd3a.transition.description=no outlier found results\: ${output} 79b9fd77-bdb7-4c47-b4aa-7af09961cfde.44aa3d4a-aea0-488a-ba6f-bf051c877834.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 79b9fd77-bdb7-4c47-b4aa-7af09961cfde.479bdeb1-d29a-4e78-a88c-d28ceb01d16b.transition.description=outliers found. Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Inputs\: table - The tale to analyze. rowDelimiter - A delimiter that separates rows in the table. columnDelimiter - A delimiter that separates columns in the table. header-A columnDelimiter separated list of The names of columns. rowNames - The name of each row of data. Returns\: An html formatted statisticall analysis of the table. ExtraResults\: means - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column means. medians - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column medians. stddevs - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column standard deviations. zValues - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column z values. Responses\: success - the operation completed successfully. failure - failed to process the list or something went wrong. 79b9fd77-bdb7-4c47-b4aa-7af09961cfde.845ad331-3a9e-486d-afdb-e2675e41c952.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifyData - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifydata to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processing tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requiring authentication. password - The password for username. Compares the loads of a list of windows servers. Useful for checking windows cluster load balancing.

Inputs\:
hosts - hosts to check.
delimiter - delimiter for hosts.
username - username for hosts.
password - password for hosts.
notifyMethod - How to report gathered information.

Returns\:
An html report.

Responses\:
success - no problems found.
diagnosed - potential problems found.
failure - something went wrong.
